		<title>04The Misery Seats</title>
		<content>     These seats are a most unusual    
 feature in an English Church, being   
 usually found in monasteries where    
 their arm supports and "tip-up" seats 
 allowed old or tired monks to support 
 themselves when they had to stand. The
 word 'misery' came from their original
 name of misericords which in turn came
 from a Latin word meaning pity _in    
 this case pity for the old tired      
 monks.                                
     The seats are beautifully carved  
 and well worth a visit.               
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
                                       
